    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Tom Wicker is right that it is time to remember the forgotten victims of Attica, meaning the hostages whom law officers shot while storming the prison, and their widows and children (Op-Ed, Sept. 23).</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Tom Wicker is right that it is time to remember the forgotten victims of Attica, meaning the hostages whom law officers shot while storming the prison, and their widows and children (Op-Ed, Sept. 23).</p>
        <p>The inmates the law officers assaulted deserve the compensation they have recently been awarded, but it is anomalous indeed for victims who were serving time to be paid while victims who were serving the state and people of New York have been neither compensated nor even properly thanked. If the New York Legislature has a conscience, it will recognize their sacrifice and revise its insufficient compensatory offer.</p>
        <p>MALCOLM BELL  Weston, Vt., Sept. 24, 2000</p>
        <p>The writer is a former special assistant attorney general, New York State Attica investigation.</p>
      </block>
